text: Jigme Yoser Thinley (born 9 September 1952) was the Prime Minister of Bhutan. He began his term as Prime Minister in 2008. It ended in 2013. He was succeeded by Tshering Tobgay. ==References== Category:1952 births Category:Prime ministers of Bhutan Category:Living people Category:Bhutanese politicians
